  "title": "Quality Control Manager (Electrical)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<p><br>\nThe role involves overseeing QC engineers, implementing QA/QC procedures, and ensuring all electrical installations meet project, industry, and statutory requirements.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Lead and manage the QC (Electrical) team in executing quality control activities for electrical works.</li>\n  <li>Develop, review, and approve quality procedures, inspection test plans (ITPs), and method statements.</li>\n  <li>Oversee inspections, testing, and audits of electrical equipment, cabling, and installations.</li>\n  <li>Ensure all works comply with project specifications, codes, and safety regulations.</li>\n  <li>Manage non-conformance reports (NCRs), corrective actions, and preventive measures.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with consultants, clients, and subcontractors on quality-related issues.</li>\n  <li>Maintain and manage quality documentation, inspection records, and test reports for audits and handover.</li>\n  <li>Provide technical leadership, mentoring, and guidance to QC engineers and site staff.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree/Diploma in Electrical Engineering or related discipline.</li>\n  <li>Minimum 10 years of experience in electrical quality control for large-scale construction projects, with at least 3 years in a managerial role.</li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge of LV/MV electrical systems, testing procedures, and QA/QC standards.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with Singapore codes, regulations, and authority submission requirements.</li>\n  <li>Demonstrated leadership and team management skills.</li>\n  <li>Excellent analytical, communication, and coordination abilities.</li>\n  <li>Experience in large infrastructure or industrial projects is preferred.</li>\n  <li>Willingness to work at Tuas with transportation pick up at designated MRT station.</li>\n</ul>",
